'''Anand Kumar''' (born 1 January 1973) is an [[India]]n Mathematics [[educator]] best known for his [[Super 30]] programme, which he started in [[Patna]], [[Bihar]] in 2002, and which coaches underprivileged students for [[IIT-JEE]], the entrance examination for the [[Indian Institutes of Technology]] ([[Indian Institutes of Technology|IITs]]). By 2018, 422 out of 481 students had made it to the IITs and [[Discovery Channel]] showcased his work in a documentary.<ref name="hindustantimes">{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/education/jee-advanced-result-2017-it-is-30-30-for-anand-kumar-s-super-30/story-ZcXXIfQfg20qqHtyXgwERN.html|title=JEE Advanced result 2017: It is 30/30 for Anand Kumar’s Super 30|date=12 June 2017|work=Hindustan Times|access-date=13 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170613154230/http://www.hindustantimes.com/education/jee-advanced-result-2017-it-is-30-30-for-anand-kumar-s-super-30/story-ZcXXIfQfg20qqHtyXgwERN.html|archive-date=13 June 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="di">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-03-14/patna/28000386_1_crack-iit-jee-super-30-discovery-communications-india|title=Discovery to showcase Super-30 today|date=14 March 2009|work=The Times of India|first1=Pranava K|last1=Chaudhary|access-date=30 June 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130630105823/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-03-14/patna/28000386_1_crack-iit-jee-super-30-discovery-communications-india|archive-date=30 June 2013|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="telegraphindia">{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050222/asp/frontpage/story_4407084.asp|title=Living the vilayat dream at home – Teacher who failed to study abroad coaches students to do so|date=22 February 2005|work=The Telegraph|access-date=15 May 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090923213719/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050222/asp/frontpage/story_4407084.asp|archive-date=23 September 2009|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="bc">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/5345100.stm|title=Helping poor Indians crack toughest test|date=21 September 2006|work=BBC News|first=Amarnath|last=Tewary|access-date=15 May 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100529101336/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/5345100.stm|archive-date=29 May 2010|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Super 30 does it again: 28 of its students crack JEE Advanced|url= http://www.hindustantimes.com/education/super-30-does-it-again-29-of-its-students-crack-jee-advanced/story-NusjppZ3LFxjZ9EKqWTstO.html|newspaper= Hindustan Times|date= 12 June 2016|access-date= 27 June 2016|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160622070733/http://www.hindustantimes.com/education/super-30-does-it-again-29-of-its-students-crack-jee-advanced/story-NusjppZ3LFxjZ9EKqWTstO.html|archive-date= 22 June 2016|url-status= live}}</ref> Kumar has spoken at [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology|MIT]] and [[Harvard University|Harvard]] about his programs for students from the underprivileged sections of Indian society.<ref name="Super 30 founder Anand Kumar invited to speak at MIT and Harvard ">{{cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/super-30-founder-anand-kumar-invited-to-speak-at-mit-and-harvard/articleshow/43795140.cms|title=Super 30 founder Anand Kumar invited to speak at MIT and Harvard|date=29 September 2014|work=The Economic Times India|access-date=29 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141001143331/http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/super-30-founder-anand-kumar-invited-to-speak-at-mit-and-harvard/articleshow/43795140.cms|archive-date=1 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Kumar and his school have been the subject of several [[smear campaigns]], some of which have been carried in Indian media sources.<ref name="thehindu2018"/> His life and work are portrayed in the 2019 film, ''[[Super 30 (film)|Super 30]]'', where Kumar is played by [[Hrithik Roshan]].<ref name="it"/>

==ᱯᱩᱭᱞᱩ ᱡᱤᱭᱚᱱ==
Kumar was born in [[Patna]], [[Bihar]], India. His father was a clerk<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://getahead.rediff.com/report/2009/dec/15/meet-anand-kumar-of-super-30.htm |title=Archived copy |access-date=15 December 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091217080621/http://getahead.rediff.com/report/2009/dec/15/meet-anand-kumar-of-super-30.htm |archive-date=17 December 2009 |url-status=live }}</ref> in the postal department of India. His father could not afford private schooling for his children, and Anand attended a [[Hindi]] medium government school, where he developed his deep interest in mathematics.<ref name="careers360">{{cite web|url=http://getahead.rediff.com/report/2009/dec/15/meet-anand-kumar-of-super-30.htm|title=He trains India's poorest students for the IIT|work=Careers360|date=15 December 2009|accessdate=15 December 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091217080621/http://getahead.rediff.com/report/2009/dec/15/meet-anand-kumar-of-super-30.htm|archive-date=17 December 2009|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Super 30 Founder Anand Kumar, a Mathematician on a Mission">{{cite web |url=http://www.successstories.co.in/super-30-founder-anand-kumar-a-mathematician-on-a-mission/ |title=Super 30 Founder Anand Kumar, a Mathematician on a Mission |publisher=Success Stories |date=28 May 2012 |access-date=25 September 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121107065509/http://www.successstories.co.in/super-30-founder-anand-kumar-a-mathematician-on-a-mission/ |archive-date=7 November 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> In childhood, he studied in Patna High School, [[Patna]], [[Bihar]]. During graduation, Kumar submitted papers on [[number theory]], which were published in ''[[Mathematical Spectrum]]''.{{citation needed|date=September 2019}} He also sent a letter to the editor of ''[[The Mathematical Gazette]]''<ref name="appliedProbabilityTrust">{{citeweb|url=http://www.appliedprobability.org/content.aspx?Group=ms&Page=MS254|title=Letter to the Editor: Happy numbers (page 122 and 123)|url-status=live}}</ref> during his graduation days.

Kumar secured admission to [[University of Cambridge]], but could not attend because of his father's death and his financial condition,<ref name="careers360"/><ref name="tribune">{{cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2009/20090614/spectrum/main2.htm|title=Genius at work|work=The Sunday Tribune|first=Uttam|last=Sengupta|date=14 June 2009|accessdate=11 July 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090923144049/http://www.tribuneindia.com/2009/20090614/spectrum/main2.htm|archive-date=23 September 2009|url-status=live}}</ref> even after seeking sponsors in 1994–1995, both in Patna and Delhi.<ref name=hin/>

Kumar would work on mathematics during day time and sell ''[[papad]]s'' in evenings with his mother, who had started a business from home, to support her family.<ref name="careers360"/> Kumar tutored students to earn extra funds. Since Patna University library did not have foreign journals, Kumar would travel every weekend on a six-hour train journey to [[Varanasi]], where his younger brother, learning violin under N. Rajam, had a hostel room, so that he could work there. {{citation needed|date=October 2018}}

==ᱥᱤᱨᱯᱷᱟ.==
On 8 November 2018, Anand Kumar was honoured with the Global Education Award<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://globaleducationawards.com/|title=Home – Prime Time Research Media Global Education Awards, Market Research Company|website=globaleducationawards.com|access-date=7 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190307173908/http://globaleducationawards.com/|archive-date=7 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> 2018 by [[Malabar Gold and Diamonds|Malabar Gold & Diamonds]] in [[Dubai]]. His efforts in the field of education are considered "pioneering". Anand Kumar has been felicitated in the US with  "Education Excellence Award 2019 " by the [[Foundation for Excellence in Education|Foundation For Excellence in Education]] ([[Foundation for Excellence in Education|FFE]]) at a function in [[San Jose, California]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Rashtriya Bal Kalyan Award presented to Super-30 founder |url= https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/nri/nris-in-news/super-30-founder-anand-kumar-felicitated-in-us/articleshow/71194746.cms
|newspaper= The Economic Times |date= 19 September 2019}}</ref>

